  "instructions": [
    "preheat the oven to 400f (200c).",
    "season the pork tenderloin with salt, black pepper, and allspice.",
    "heat the olive oil in a large oven-safe pan over medium-high heat.",
    "cook the pork tenderloin for 2-3 minutes on each side, or until browned.",
    "transfer the pan to the preheated oven and roast for 10-12 minutes, or until cooked through.",
    "while the pork is cooking, boil the sliced potatoes in a large pot of salted water until tender.",
    "drain the potatoes and add the chopped onion, minced garlic, ground cumin, smoked paprika, salt, and black pepper.",
    "mix well to combine.",
    "remove the pork from the oven and let it rest for 5 minutes before slicing.",
    "serve the sliced pork with the boiled potato mixture, drizzled with lemon juice.",
    "garnish with chopped fresh parsley or cilantro, if desired."
  ],
